text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia patagiata is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt, Great Southern and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The rounded shrub typically grows to a height of 0.5 to 2.5 metres (2 to 8 ft). It blooms from July to September and produces yellow flowers.
